On February 13 \textit{The Oshkosh Northwester} listed the length of daylight as 10 hours and 24 minutes, the sunrise was $6:57 \textsc{am}$, and the sunset as $8:15 \textsc{pm}$. The length of daylight and sunrise were correct, but the sunset was wrong. When did the sun really set?\\
\\
$\textbf{(A)}\hspace{.05in}5:10 \textsc{pm} \quad \textbf{(B)}\hspace{.05in}5:21 \textsc{pm} \quad \textbf{(C)}\hspace{.05in}5:41\textsc{pm} \quad \textbf{(D)}\hspace{.05in}5:57 \textsc{pm} \quad \textbf{(E)}\hspace{.05in}6:03 \textsc{pm} $
